0&TPL=NA&SUB=0&d1=0&GID=837937 NS], [http://www12.statcan.ca/english/census06/data/topics/RetrieveProductTable.cfm?Temporal=2006&PID=89122&METH=1&APATH=3&PTYPE=88971&THEME=73&AID=&FREE=0&FOCUS=&VID=0&GC=99&GK=NA&RL=0&TPL=NA&SUB=0&d1=0&GID=837934 PE], [http://www12.statcan.ca/english/census06/data/topics/RetrieveProductTable.cfm?Temporal=2006&PID=89122&METH=1&APATH=3&PTYPE=88971&THEME=73&AID=&FREE=0&FOCUS=&VID=0&GC=99&GK=NA&RL=0&TPL=NA&SUB=0&d1=0&GID=837929 NL], [http://www12.statcan.ca/english/census06/data/topics/RetrieveProductTable.cfm?Temporal=2006&PID=89122&METH=1&APATH=3&PTYPE=88971&THEME=73&AID=&FREE=0&FOCUS=&VID=0&GC=99&GK=NA&RL=0&TPL=NA&SUB=0&d1=0&GID=838089 YT], [http://www12.statcan.ca/english/census06/data/topics/RetrieveProductTable.cfm?Temporal=2006&PID=89122&METH=1&APATH=3&PTYPE=88971&THEME=73&AID=&FREE=0&FOCUS=&VID=0&GC=99&GK=NA&RL=0&TPL=NA&SUB=0&d1=0&GID=838091 NT], [http://www12.statcan.ca/english/census06/data/topics/RetrieveProductTable.cfm?Temporal=2006&PID=89122&METH=1&APATH=3&PTYPE=88971&THEME=73&AID=&FREE=0&FOCUS=&VID=0&GC=99&GK=NA&RL=0&TPL=NA&SUB=0&d1=0&GID=838093 NU]Retrieved 2009-10-05.</ref><ref>[http://www12.statcan.ca/english/census06/analysis/aboriginal/tables/table2.htm Number and percentage of population reporting Aboriginal identity, Canada, provinces and territories, 2006]Retrieved 2009-10-05.</ref><ref>[http://www12.statcan.ca/english/census06/analysis/aboriginal/charts/chart1.htm Percentage of Aboriginal people in the population, Canada, provinces and territories, 2006 ] Retrieved 2009-10-05.</ref>
|}
<small>
:A.{{Note|A}}% of the provincial or territorial population that is Aboriginal
:B.{{Note|B}}% of Canada's population that is Aboriginal
:C.{{Note|C}}According to Statistics Canada this figure "Includes those who identified themselves as Registered Indians and/or band members without identifying themselves as North American Indian, M<U+00E9>tis or Inuit in the Aboriginal identity question."<ref name="breakdown"/></small>
[[Image:Nordamerikanische Kulturareale en.png|thumb|upright|alt="Colour coded map of North America showing the classification of indigenious peoples of North America according to Alfred Kroeber showing the areas of Arctic, Subarctic, Northwest Coast, Northeast Woodlands, Plains, Plateau"|Cultural areas of North American Indigenous peoples at the time of European contact.]]
[[Ethnography|Ethnographers]] commonly classify indigenous peoples of the Americas in the United States and Canada into ten geographical regions, [[cultural area]]s, with shared cultural traits.<ref>{{cite web
  | title =Civilization.ca-Gateway to Aboriginal Heritage-Culture Areas Index
  | work =  Canadian Museum of Civilization Corporation
  | publisher =Government of Canada
  | date = May 12, 2006
  | url = http://www.civilization.ca/cmc/exhibitions/tresors/ethno/etb0170e.shtml
  | accessdate =2009-10-06 }}
</ref> The Canadian regions are:

*Arctic
*Subarctic
*Northwest Coast
*Northeast Woodlands
*Plains
*Plateau

In the 20th century the First Nations population of Canada increased tenfold.<ref name="statcan_aboriginal_demographics">{{cite web
  | title = Aboriginal peoples of Canada: A demographic profile
  | work = Statistics Canada
  | publisher = 
  | date = 2001
  | url = http://www12.statcan.ca/english/census01/Products/Analytic/companion/abor/canada.cfm
  | accessdate =2009-10-02 }}
</ref> Between 1900 and 1950 the population grew by 29%.  After the 1960s the [[infant mortality]] level on reserves dropped dramatically and the population grew by 161%.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://hannahroper.com/Social.html |title=Social|work=Aboriginal Nationalism| accessdate =2009-10-15 }}</ref><ref name=babies/> Since the 1980s the number of First Nations babies more than doubled and currently almost half of the First Nations population is under the age of 25.<ref name=babies>{{cite web |url=http://www12.statcan.ca/english/census01/Products/Analytic/companion/abor/canada.cfm|title=Aboriginal peoples of Canada|work=Statistics Canada | accessdate =2009-10-05 }}</ref><ref name="statcan_aboriginal_demographics" />

